definitions.definition: ( operations ) The process of planning , implementing , and controlling the efficient , effective flow and storage of goods, services and related information from their point of origin to point of consumption for the purpose of satisfying customer requirements.
( military ) The procurement , supply , maintenance , and transportation of equipment , facilities , and personnel .
